246
00:16:08,000 --> 00:16:11,000
There are many serious hazards working at heights.

247
00:16:11,000 --> 00:16:14,000
This is probably the most important message of the safety standard.

248
00:16:14,000 --> 00:16:17,000
To erect trusses, you have to work at heights.

249
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:20,000
The main thrust of the safety standard is to allow erectors

250
00:16:20,000 --> 00:16:23,000
to walk the trusses under controlled conditions.

251
00:16:25,000 --> 00:16:29,000
When trusses are erected at up to 600 millimetre centres,

252
00:16:29,000 --> 00:16:31,000
you can, under controlled conditions,

253
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:34,000
use the bottom cords of erected and braced trusses

254
00:16:34,000 --> 00:16:37,000
as access and fore protection.

255
00:16:37,000 --> 00:16:40,000
At no time is any person to stand on

256
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:43,000
or work from an external wall top plate

257
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:46,000
without suitable fore protection.

258
