You can use trusses, but a no-go zone applies.

259
00:16:52,000 --> 00:16:55,000
No one can work in the area of the erected framing

260
00:16:55,000 --> 00:16:58,000
where the height from the top of the bottom cord

261
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:02,000
to the top of the top cord is less than 900 mills.

262
00:17:02,000 --> 00:17:07,000
No one can work within 1.2 metres of the outside wall top plate.

263
00:17:07,000 --> 00:17:10,000
If you're any closer than 1200,

264
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:13,000
when you fall, you pass your waist

265
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:15,000
and you'll end up going straight over the roof.

266
00:17:15,000 --> 00:17:17,000
So always work 1200 back off the plate,

267
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:19,000
which is a zone where if you fall,

268
00:17:19,000 --> 00:17:22,000
everyone's from feet to waist is about 1200.

269
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:24,000
So you will not go straight over.

270
00:17:24,000 --> 00:17:26,000
It is a catch zone where you grab hold of the plate

271
00:17:26,000 --> 00:17:28,000
or land on the plate and save yourself.

272
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Staying in a position where you can't fall out of the building

273
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:33,000
or can't fall through into the building

274
00:17:33,000 --> 00:17:35,000
is the key of the no-go zone.

275
00:17:36,000 --> 00:17:38,000
To manage the risk of falls,

276
00:17:38,000 --> 00:17:41,000
you have to follow the following conditions.

277
00:17:42,000 --> 00:17:46,000
Have the trusses braced at a maximum of 3 metres.

278
00:17:46,000 --> 00:17:48,000
You have to be a competent person,

279
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:51,000
fully trained to walk the trusses.

280
00:17:51,000 --> 00:17:54,000
You have to have suitable footwear

281
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:57,000
that provides a good foothold.

282
00:17:57,000 --> 00:18:00,000
You need to be supervised by a competent person

283
00:18:00,000 --> 00:18:02,000
in the erection team.

284
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:05,000
The bottom cord has to be checked for defects.

285
00:18:09,000 --> 00:18:12,000
Erecting trusses is different from a lot of other work

286
00:18:12,000 --> 00:18:14,000
in construction,

287
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:16,000
but the risk of falling is ever-present

288
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:18,000
and has to be managed.

289
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:21,000
This way of using the trusses for fall protection

290
00:18:21,000 --> 00:18:24,000
is practical, but you have to follow the guidelines

291
00:18:24,000 --> 00:18:26,000
to make it safe.

292
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:30,000
Some trusses are tall and you have to work near the top.

293
00:18:30,000 --> 00:18:33,000
If the apex or other high bracing points

294
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
cannot be reached,

295
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:38,000
use whaling plates to reach the apex or high points.

296
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:40,000
Fix whaling plates for standing

297
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:43,000
or supporting temporary work platforms

298
00:18:43,000 --> 00:18:45,000
at the appropriate height.

299
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:48,000
The whaling plate should be fixed to the face of the truss

300
00:18:48,000 --> 00:18:51,000
according to the manufacturer's recommendations

301
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:54,000
to ensure the load is transferred to the bottom cord.

302
00:18:55,000 --> 00:18:57,000
The whaling plate should be timber

303
00:18:57,000 --> 00:19:00,000
of 70 by 35mm F5

304
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:02,000
or equivalent

305
00:19:02,000 --> 00:19:05,000
to a maximum of 1500mm long.

306
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:10,000
Fixed at each end by a minimum of 265mm

307
00:19:10,000 --> 00:19:13,000
by 3.15mm nails.

308
00:19:20,000 --> 00:19:22,000
If we are using ladders for access,

309
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,000
they should have non-slip feet

310
00:19:24,000 --> 00:19:27,000
and be secured against displacement.

311
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:29,000
There should be a safe landing place

312
00:19:29,000 --> 00:19:31,000
when stepping off the ladder,

313
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:33,000
and the top of the ladder should extend

314
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:36,000
1 metre above the landing place.

315
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:40,000
You can use timber railings

316
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:43,000
installed at the point of manufacture.

317
00:19:43,000 --> 00:19:45,000
You can install temporary studs.

318
00:19:45,000 --> 00:19:47,000
Temporary timber handrails should be checked

319
00:19:47,000 --> 00:19:49,000
for their quality and their effectiveness

320
00:19:49,000 --> 00:19:51,000
to prevent falls.

321
00:19:53,000 --> 00:19:55,000
We can use scaffolding

322
00:19:55,000 --> 00:19:58,000
as good edge protection on low pitched roofs,

323
00:19:58,000 --> 00:20:00,000
providing the guard rails of the scaffolding

324
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
extend at least 900mm above the roof.

325
00:20:05,000 --> 00:20:07,000
Or scaffolding over 4 metres

326
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:10,000
needs to be constructed by a qualified scaffolder

327
00:20:10,000 --> 00:20:12,000
and comply with standards.

328
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,000
The first floor perimeter edge protection

329
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:17,000
must not be removed until all openings

330
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:20,000
and penetrations are otherwise protected.

331
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:23,000
Temporary timber handrails should be checked

332
00:20:23,000 --> 00:20:25,000
for their quality and their effectiveness

333
00:20:25,000 --> 00:20:28,000
to prevent falls.

334
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Where a void exists,

335
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,000
no one is to work on the first floor or above

336
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:38,000
unless a void protection system is installed.

337
00:20:43,000 --> 00:20:45,000
If you want to be safe all the time,

338
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:47,000
everyone has to be trained and qualified

339
00:20:47,000 --> 00:20:49,000
and consulted.

